reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States üá∫üá∏ on March 16, 2023
reviews.title: Beautiful Piece of Very Useful Apple Tech (as Usual)
reviews.review: I decided to do a big upgrade from my 2013 iPad Mini 2 since it‚Äôs no longer supported and is pretty much a paperweight now. The Air 5 is a gorgeous addition to my Apple family. The screen is crisp, the sound quality is excellent and can get pretty loud compared to my Mini 2 and iPhone 12. The metallic blue is stunning and is a nice change from my usual grey and black tech. Kind of bummed I can‚Äôt use my dozens of lightning cables, but the USBC charges really fast and the charging block is much appreciated since there was never one included with one the newer iPhones lol. I did go ahead and upgrade to the 256GB since I keep my iPads for so long, it really was the most cost effective option, and running out of space is very frustrating when you get that dreaded notification‚Ä¶ especially with such a versatile item like an iPad.I think people need to be more careful when checking out, make sure you are ordering NEW. Don‚Äôt click the cheaper option under the more expensive price, it‚Äôll arrive as a used iPad. I ordered a NEW iPad at the full Amazon price (which I noticed fluctuates daily depending on stock, but I got it about $100 less than the Apple Store!) and I received a brand new, sealed iPad Air 5 as I expected and ordered. My only complaint is that I ordered the iPad on 2/20 and it didn‚Äôt ship until 3/5 so make sure you‚Äôre not in a time crunch when ordering.(Thank you Amazon for shipping iPads to APO/FPO as Apple does not, the exchange has been out of stock for months in store and online, and overseas locally iPads are much more expensive here.)

reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States üá∫üá∏ on March 31, 2023
reviews.title: Perfect! So fast!
reviews.review: Fast shipping, and the tablet looks perfect.- iPad Air 5..My iPad 5 has gotten slow after 6 years, so I decided to get an upgrade. I was just expecting same one only faster.  The screen is beautiful, the speed is lightning fast, and with the thinner bezel it‚Äôs lots bigger it seems. It transferred all my other ipad and updated in less than 45 minutes.It‚Äôs much lighter and has options and apps my old 5th didn‚Äôt have. It also has battery of 10 hours, as my old one was 50% after 2 hours.  Great deal.

reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States üá∫üá∏ on March 2, 2023
reviews.title: Great Processor, and Touch ID is Back!!!
reviews.review: I love iPads.  I bought my first one back with the very first generation came out.  Since then I've owned a Gen 3 (original), and Air 2, and now this awesome Air 5.I bought the Air 2 back in December 2015, and have used it regularly ever since.  I finally decided to get a new one after Apple stopped updating the iPadOS for the Air 2.I am looking forward to another seven (or more!) years of good service from this Air 5.  The specs on that M1 chip are awesome - I've used a Mac Mini with an M1 and been really impressed.I have used my church's Air 5 for a while running Playback (Multitracks) with great results.  I plan to use mine to do the same, as well as control my PreSonus AI console.And I am VERY excited to find out that touch ID is back!  The top button is now capable of doing fingerprint ID!  (Not a fan of face ID.)The iPad rocks.  This one looks like it will be a hard rocker!And a big thank you to Amazon for the unexpected sale when I was purchasing.  I was in a big-box store (the blue and yellow one) about to make a purchase and I said to myself, "Self, you should check Amazon's pricing before you buy."  I'm glad I listened to me.  At least this time, anyway.  Some of my other advice can be a bit sketchy at times.

reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States üá∫üá∏ on February 24, 2023
reviews.title: Powerful Ipad Air
reviews.review: I bought this beginning of February, and while Amazon had a delivery date of end of month, this actually arrived about a week sooner! I will compare this with the Ipad Air 4th gen which I also own.- Dimensions, weight and screen size are the same. (I dont really need 120 Hz)- Screen brightness appears to be a little bit brighter on this Ipad Air 5.- Speaker quality appears to be almost similar between the two, at least for me. Both are good.- 5th gen has more ram (8gb vs 4gb)- The M1 is more poweful than the A14.- However maybe because of the more capable processor, battery life is a little better on the Ipad Air 4.- This Ipad Air 5 Touch ID appears to be more responsive and faster than the Ipad Air 4, also the button itself appears to be more sturdier.I always use my devices with a case so I cant find out if the back of this device is ‚Äúfragile‚Äù or not. Also I havent tested other features such as transfer speeds (write and read speeds), wifi signal speeds, and the cameras quality (for that I use my phone).Overall I find this Ipad Air 5 a good option even better than the Ipad Pro 11 even if that one has better chipset, screen and other features. If you have the extra cash then you can go for the Ipad Pro 11, or wait another year maybe for the M3 Ipad Air 6.
